sp.p:
Sir, I have brought you home a Reformado;  
 

 
 
and do entreat (for what I have said unto him, and he hath fairly answered unto me) that words 
may not by you be multiplied.

 
You speak sententiously, for credit sought  
With Tradesmen, then their wares are dearer bought;  
So Gentlemen are wronged.

 
You might safer  
Have sent it so, and your own right hand with it;  
Than to have drawn my just revenge upon you.

 
That is her humour;  
Then hark you Widow, to avoid his blushes,  
Suppose I tell he has got a bastard.

My suit my Lord to her? I never moved your Lordship to it, 
Though I presume she may be a happy fortune to one of my condition; 
a poor and younger brother; only made rich and happy in your Lordships service, and overflowing favours.

She means that to me now, but I will take no notice; 
I will find as good a Widow in a Tavern Chimney, O 
she is a dainty Widow!

Just such a bashful puppy was my brother, his Father; I wonder how my Mother came by him; 
My Father   was right, and she was right, and I have been right, but what do I speak 
on it?

 
What metal am I of? his scorn is a Lodestone;  
No Courtship like his carelessness to me;  
And all dispraise speaks for him,  
Sir I will speak with you.

 
No, let me entreat you.  
Be that way charitable, and speak worse;  
The worse the better.
